    <text type="letter">
        <body>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001r" facs="loc.02116.001_large.jpg" type="recto"/>
            <opener>
                <dateline>
                    <name type="place">Post Hospital</name>
                    <name type="place">Natchez, Miss</name>
                    <date when="1867-12-23">Dec 23d, 1867<ptr target="loc.02116_n1"/></date>
                </dateline>
                <salute>Walt Whitman;</salute>
                <salute>Dear Sir,</salute>
            </opener>
            <p>I write this, to let you know, how glad I am Walt Whitman was born; and that he
                writes&#8212;Oh! that there were more of the same sort, our country needs them. I
                hope some day to grasp your hand, and hear you speak.</p>
            <p>"<hi rend="underline">Democracy</hi>"<ptr target="duk.00508_n12"/> made me yell with
                delight; it put things into shape that I ran all in a heap before.</p>
            <p>Go on, and may God bless you and your efforts, as a true American.</p>
            <closer>
                <salute>Respectfully</salute>
                <signed>F. B. Gillette</signed>
                <signed>acting <gap reason="illegible" quantity="1" unit="word"/> in chg&#8212;</signed>
            </closer>
            <pb xml:id="leaf001v" facs="loc.02116.002_large.jpg" type="verso"/>
